#. <section class="sutta" id="sn27.10"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn27.10:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 27"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn27.10:0.2"
msgid "1. Kilesavagga"
msgstr "1. Corruptions"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn27.10:0.3"
msgid "10. Khandhasutta"
msgstr "10. The Aggregates"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn27.10:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ."
msgstr "At Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "sn27.10:1.2"
msgid ""
"“Yo, bhikkhave, rūpasmiṃ chandarāgo, cittasseso upakkileso … pe … yo "
"viññāṇasmiṃ chandarāgo, cittasseso upakkileso."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, desire and greed for form, feeling, perception, choices, or "
"consciousness is a corruption of the mind."

msgctxt "sn27.10:1.3"
msgid ""
"Yato kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno imesu pañcasu ṭhānesu cetaso upakkileso "
"pahīno hoti, nekkhammaninnañcassa cittaṃ hoti."
msgstr ""
"When a mendicant has given up mental corruption in these five cases, their "
"mind inclines to renunciation."

msgctxt "sn27.10:1.4"
msgid ""
"Nekkhammaparibhāvitaṃ cittaṃ kammaniyaṃ khāyati, abhiññā sacchikaraṇīyesu "
"dhammesū”ti."
msgstr ""
"A mind imbued with renunciation is declared to be capable of directly "
"knowing anything that can be realized.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn27.10:1.5"
msgid "Dasamaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn27.10:1.6"
msgid "Kilesavaggo paṭhamo."
msgstr ""

#. </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pli3.235"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn27.10:2.1"
msgid "Cakkhu rūpañca viññāṇaṃ,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn27.10:2.2"
msgid "phasso ca vedanāya ca;"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn27.10:2.3"
msgid "Saññā ca cetanā taṇhā,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn27.10:2.4"
msgid "dhātu khandhena te dasāti."
msgstr ""

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsutta">
msgctxt "sn27.10:2.5"
msgid "Kilesasaṃyuttaṃ samattaṃ."
msgstr "The Linked Discourses on corruptions are complete."
